text: Their pizzas here are delicious! We decided to give it a try after finding out that they offer vegan cheese, which is the only way my son can have pizza due to his severe lactose intolerance. They hand toss the dough in front of you and add ‚Ä¶More

name: Sam Attar
text:
Ordered double order of Wings and they made it just right. well done, Dry, sauce on the side. they didn't put the lid on it. so it stayed crispy. I was so excited to eat them the photo doesn't do them justice.
Just perfect! Thanks

name: Camdyn Rasque
text: As far as pizza goes it's pretty good, miles better than the big pizza chains. The whole pizzas a fairly pricey but if you go in for lunch and only order a slice or two the price is very reasonable. They also have a very nice selection of bottled sodas if you aren't into fountain soda. (But they do have both)

name: Ed Resha
text: When we go for great pizza, we are hooked on this place. All organic veggie toppings and the sauce is bursting with flavor. there are plenty of cheap pizzas around but this place is great. Don't forget their fresh salads.

name: Edward Rutherford
text: Great pizza.. little more expensive than other places.. some different varieties.. but not much room inside..

name: Odins Pride
text: Good deals. Fresh pizza. Polite staff. Ask for fresh slices however, sometime they get busy and cannot have them ready when you arrive. Wait a few min and bam delicious fresh slices Everytime.

text: Cheap lunch options. Slice of pizza, salad, and half sandwich for about $7. Pizzas not too greasy, which is nice.
